conexp.fx.core.context.temporal

Class TemporalContext<G,M>

  • java.lang.Object
    • conexp.fx.core.context.temporal.TemporalContext<G,M>
  • Type Parameters:
    G -
    M - a prototypical implementation of a temporal context the time dimension is assumed to be a finite prefix of the natural numbers, ie. the timepoints 0 to n for some natural number n Furthermore it is assumed that all timepoints have the same objects and attributes. If this is not the case, then it can be ensured by calling the normalize() methode. It simply adds all existing objects and attributes to all other timepoint contexts.

    public class TemporalContext<G,M>
extends Object
